30/09/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Monday (29 September), Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul met with his Bulgarian counterpart, Nikolai Svinarov, to discuss participation in the international security force in Iraq.
Gonul praised Bulgaria's decision to send a peacekeeping battalion and said he expects a draft resolution on Turkey's participation, probably next week.
On a different note, the defence minister said Turkey fully supports Bulgaria's bid to become a member of NATO.
(Anadolu Agency, BTA, NTV - 29/09/03)
